        "title": "fix(models): filter models list by configured providers in replace mode [AI-assisted]",
        "body": "### Summary\nThis PR fixes an issue where the output of `openclaw models list` is not filtered when `models.mode: \"replace\"` is configured with a restricted list of providers.\n\n### Changes\n- Implemented `isProviderAllowed` helper in `src/commands/models/list.rows.ts` to check if a provider is allowed under the current `models.mode` config.\n- Updated `matchesRowFilter` and `appendConfiguredRows` to filter out model rows for providers not explicitly present in `models.providers` when `models.mode` is set to `\"replace\"`.\n- Added unit tests in `src/commands/models/list.rows.test.ts` to verify filtering behavior.\n\n### Real behavior proof\nBelow is the output of the unit test verification:\n```\n ✓  commands  ../../src/commands/models/list.rows.test.ts (5 tests) 5565ms\n     ✓ can skip runtime model-suppression hooks for provider-catalog fast paths  1865ms\n     ✓ applies manifest suppression when runtime model-suppression hooks are skipped  756ms\n     ✓ uses Codex auth availability for configured canonical OpenAI rows  757ms\n     ✓ filters out providers not in models.providers when mode is replace  1442ms\n     ✓ keeps provider normalization for configured provider models  723ms\n```\n",
